<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is a partial list of=C2=A0things that Elo=
n Musk has thought are the most important things in the world:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">=E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https://link.mail=
.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34589760.257369/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY25iYy5jb20vMj=
AxOC8xMS8wNS9lbG9uLW11c2stdGVzbGFzLXdvcmstaXMtaW1wb3J0YW50LXRvLXRoZS1mdXR1c=
mUtb2YtdGhlLXdvcmxkLmh0bWw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB23f5f310" itemprop=3D"S=
toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000=
; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom=
-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Solvi=
ng the environment</a>,=E2=80=9D by building electric cars at Tesla.</li>=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Making humanity a =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"=
https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34589760.257369/aHR0cHM6Ly93d=
3cuY25iYy5jb20vMjAyMS8wNC8yMy9lbG9uLW11c2stYWltaW5nLWZvci1tYXJzLXNvLWh1bWFu=
aXR5LWlzLW5vdC1hLXNpbmdsZS1wbGFuZXQtc3BlY2llcy5odG1s/607f07ceef4b8524a319a2=
3cB31d730e6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blan=
k" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom=
-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; back=
ground-color: #ccc;">multi-planet species</a>,=E2=80=9D by building spacesh=
ips at SpaceX.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Buying Twitter=C2=
=A0to prevent the =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.c=
om/click/34589760.257369/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2ZnYXRlLmNvbS9sb2NhbC9hcnRpY2xlL2=
Vsb24tbXVzay1jbGFpbS1mb3ItYnV5aW5nLXR3aXR0ZXItc2YtbWluZC12aXJ1cy0xODQ2MjE3M=
i5waHA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB446b1f46" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">corrosive effect on civi=
lization</a>=E2=80=9D of San Francisco=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Cmind virus.=E2=80=
=9D</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I want to make a few points about this list. F=
irst: It=E2=80=99s a fine list? Stopping climate change, colonizing space, =
and=C2=A0changing public discourse are all=C2=A0reasonable things to priori=
tize.=C2=A0There are tech founders who are like =E2=80=9CI wanted to solve =
the problem that sometimes when I order food delivery, it arrives cold=E2=
=80=9D; Elon Musk is=C2=A0not a founder like that.<a class=3D"footnote-inde=
x" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !imp=
ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; displa=
y: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Second: He has made a lot of progress on these=
 problems.=C2=A0Tesla revolutionized electric cars; SpaceX revolutionized s=
pace; I personally do not care for the effect that Musk has had on the conv=
ersation at Twitter (now X), but he sure has had an effect, and I assume <e=
m>he=E2=80=99s=C2=A0</em>happy with it. As a founder of companies intended =
to solve big problems, Elon Musk has been quite effective.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is obvious stuff.=C2=A0=E2=80=9CElon Musk=
 tackles big problems and is unusually good at solving them=E2=80=9D is jus=
t conventional wisdom, which is why there are=C2=A0glowing biographies writ=
ten about him and=C2=A0some days he=E2=80=99s the richest person in the wor=
ld. The main way to get really rich is by solving big problems successfully=
.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And that=E2=80=99s the third point that I want=
 to make about this list: When Elon Musk has looked around and identified a=
 big problem and set about trying to solve it, he has done so by founding (=
or acquiring) a for-profit company that he owns and controls.<a class=3D"fo=
otnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration=
: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; =
border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !import=
ant; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>=C2=A0This is not the only way to (try to) solve big problems. Bill Gat=
es, for instance, got very rich by selling software=C2=A0and then decided t=
o improve the world by donating a lot of money <a href=3D"https://link.mail=
.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34589760.257369/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ2F0ZXNmb3VuZG=
F0aW9uLm9yZy9vdXItd29yaw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB978b61b6" itemprop=3D"Sto=
ryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; =
text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-c=
olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> to cha=
ritable works</a>. Or various billionaires try to improve the world by supp=
orting politicians who they think will do good things. Musk has <a href=3D"=
https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34589760.257369/aHR0cHM6Ly93d=
3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vMjAyNC8wMy8wNS91cy9wb2xpdGljcy90cnVtcC1lbG9uLW11c2suaHRt=
bA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB929d6c4d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"i=
temscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none =
!important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-=
bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">dabbled</a> in these approach=
es, but mostly they are not his preference. =E2=80=9C=E2=80=98<a href=3D"ht=
tps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34589760.257369/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3c=
uY25uLmNvbS8yMDIzLzA5LzExL3RlY2gvZWxvbi1tdXNrLWJpbGwtZ2F0ZXMtaXNhYWNzb24tYm=
9vay9pbmRleC5odG1sIzp-OnRleHQ9TXVzayUyMHRvbGQlMjBJc2FhY3NvbiUyMGhlJTIwZmVsd=
CxhJTIwc2hvcnQlMjBiZXQlMjBhZ2FpbnN0JTIwVGVzbGEu/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB4f=
b609fd" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" st=
yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgroun=
d-color: #ccc;">Most philanthropy was bulls=E2=80=94</a>,=E2=80=99=C2=A0Mus=
k told Gates=E2=80=9D once,=C2=A0arguing that Tesla did more good for the w=
orld than most charities.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And this too is a pretty common view.=C2=A0It =
is not the only view =E2=80=94=C2=A0a lot of people think that philanthropy=
 is good! =E2=80=94=C2=A0but in Silicon Valley tech circles it is <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34589760.257369/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cubW90aGVyam9uZXMuY29tL3BvbGl0aWNzLzIwMjMvMTIvZWZmZWN0aXZlLWFjY2VsZXJh=
dGlvbmlzbS8/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB0d65af43" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" items=
cope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorati=
on: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000=
; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> fairly conventional=
</a>=C2=A0to <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34589=
760.257369/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYXhpb3MuY29tLzIwMjMvMTAvMjEvcGhpbGFudGhyb3B5LXNl=
bGZpc2gtYmlsbGlvbmFpcmVz/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB14272102" itemprop=3D"Sto=
ryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; =
text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-c=
olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> think =
that</a> startups are a better way to improve the world than charity, that =
startups can be more ambitious, more focused on results, have a better alig=
nment of interests and more motivated employees, and can raise and deploy a=
 lot more money than charities. =E2=80=9CTechnological innovation in a mark=
et system is inherently philanthropic,=E2=80=9D <a href=3D"https://link.mai=
l.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34589760.257369/aHR0cHM6Ly9hMTZ6LmNvbS90aGUtd=
GVjaG5vLW9wdGltaXN0LW1hbmlmZXN0by8/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8a73f3ed" itemp=
rop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color:=
 #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; borde=
r-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc=
;"> wrote Marc Andreessen last year</a>, in a =E2=80=9CTechno-Optimist Mani=
festo=E2=80=9D laying out this view.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Now, I don=E2=80=99t think that Musk thinks th=
at=C2=A0<em>all</em>=C2=A0profit-seeking companies, or <em>all=C2=A0</em>te=
ch startups, are good; he criticizes lots of them, and had to go and buy Tw=
itter because its previous management upset him. I just think that he think=
s the best way to improve the world is generally through=C2=A0a for-profit =
company <em>that he runs</em>. And even=C2=A0<em>this=C2=A0</em>view =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cthe highest form of philanthropy is a for-profit company =
run specifically by Elon Musk=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0is pretty widespread.=
 Larry Page <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/345897=
60.257369/aHR0cHM6Ly9ueW1hZy5jb20vaW50ZWxsaWdlbmNlci8yMDE0LzAzL2xhcnJ5LXBhZ=
2VzLWNoYXJpdHktcHJvYmxlbS5odG1s/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB5bbf4f1b" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
 has mused=C2=A0about</a>=C2=A0leaving=C2=A0his fortune to Musk, because Mu=
sk=E2=80=99s for-profit businesses are more philanthropic=C2=A0than any phi=
lanthropies he can think of.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Last week <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
rgbusiness.com/click/34589760.257369/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcG=
luaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDMtMDEvb3BlbmFpLWlzbi10LW9wZW4tZW5vdWdoLWZvci1lb=
G9uP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAzMDYyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJj=
ZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDMwNiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f=
07ceef4b8524a319a23cBbccf354f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscop=
e" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !import=
ant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-=
style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Musk sued OpenAI</a>, arguing that =
it was founded as a nonprofit organization to build artificial intelligence=
 for the benefit of humanity, that he was a big donor to that nonprofit, an=
d that it has turned into a for-profit company in violation of a supposed a=
greement not to. What I find strangest about all this is that OpenAI was a =
nonprofit to begin with: Its founders, people like Musk and Sam Altman, are=
 generally leading proponents and examples of the idea that the best way to=
 do good in the world is with a for-profit tech startup.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At some level I can understand why artificial =
intelligence is different from electric cars or rockets or <a href=3D"https=
://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34589760.257369/aHR0cHM6Ly9lbi53aW=
tpcGVkaWEub3JnL3dpa2kvTG9vcHQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7a7796a6" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
